The paper discusses learning control policies for robots using tools from generalization theory in machine learning. The focus is on obtaining upper bounds on the expected cost of control policies across novel environments, which is a problem in the supervised learning setting. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV).
